1 - Portrait Henry\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf0 Hello everyone.\
Please let me introduce you to Henry Carton de Wiart, a famous Belgian personality. He is a key component of our case-study.\
Part of a large noble family, he has been minister several times, Prime Minister, president of many councils and also a lawyer and a writer\'85 And I\'92m sure some of you know that the belgian city Li\'e8ge is also called \'91La Cit\'e9 ardente\'92. This nickname comes from one of his book. \
We could go for a while, because Henry has been very active during his life\'85\
But maybe you already see our point: there is enough information about him to observe how linked open data document his life.\
In the next slides, I will present with my colleague Ettore a close-reading analysis of linked data about that guy.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\sa280\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf0 2 - Close-reading?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf0 Usually, when we speak about Linked Data we first think about stuff like Big Data, data mining or network analysis... in one word: distant-reading approaches.\
For our presentation today, we wanted to reverse the process and choose something a little more experimental: trying a close-reading analysis of Linked Data.\
Currently, there is a lot of discussions about how archives should adapt their archival descriptions to linked data principles. However, maintaining data is known to be one of the huge challenges we\'92ll have to face.\
So, instead of observing global characteristics of linked data resources, we decided to focus on one single entity and its data quality.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\sa280\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf0 \
3 - \'91Continuum\'92\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf0 Linked data fit in a landscape of pre-existing resources.\
Online resources about Henry consist of a continuum, going from very structured data to unstructured data.\
At one end, we have the most structured data, which correspond to linked data, namely Wikidata, Viaf, DBpedia, etc.\
And at the other end are situated less structured data, like the national biography of Henry.\
In between, we find RDF triples from several archives and libraries, archival descriptions in XML or Wikpedia pages.\
Our intention was to test and confront these various sources, to observe to what extent they were consistent and complementary?\
Now I give the floor to Ettore, who will begin with the linked open data cloud.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\sa280\partightenfactor0

\b\fs28 \cf0 5. Manual triplification\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf0 After this first exploration with the help of Alex, we wanted to take a close look at the data contained in less structured resources.\
We try to do that by acting as if we were an archivist, who would like to inject biographical information into the Linked Data cloud, in other words, a manual triplification.\
We used three different types of resources: an EAC and an EAD files from the State Archives and the national biography about Henry.\
During this triplification process, we took all sentences and tried to extract and translate every single piece of information about Henry into RDF triples (subject, property, object). \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\sa280\partightenfactor0

